<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06062017 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06062017 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  FLORIDA; MULTIPLE; SHOOTING; AUTO; RENT; STORE  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  A man armed with a pistol and a shotgun killed two auto rental workers Fridayafternoon at a crowded Alamo Rent-a-Car outlet near Miami InternationalAirport, police and witnesses said.;    Witnesses said the gunman, who showedup shortly before 1 p.m. at the auto rental office, apparently chased twoAlamo employees into the parking lot, where he shot them.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  General News  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  FLORIDA GUNMAN KILLS 2 AT CAR RENTAL AGENCY  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     The gunman also shot at a police car but dropped his weapons andsurrendered when he ran out of ammunition, said witness Tony Duval, who worksat a USA Car Rental office across the street. No police officers were hit.;   Police said they arrested Lazaro Martinez, described as in his late 20s. Hehad worked at the company as a car washer for about five years, anotheremployee said. Police did not identify victims, but workers identified them asthe manager of the outlet and the manager of the facility's mechanical garage.Police would not confirm this.;    Witnesses who arrived at the office about12:55 p.m. to pick up a car said they saw people running and ducking in theparking lot.;    &quot;We were pulled up to get a rental car when we hear popping.It sounded like a .22-caliber gun,&quot; said witness Larry Bergman, a tourist fromNew York. &quot;We saw these guys run into the parking lot and realized there wasshooting going on.&quot;;    Bergman said he and his friends ducked in the van theyarrived in. After the shooting was over, they walked over to where the twobodies lay in the parking lot about 50 feet apart. One of the victims had twobullet holes in his forehead, Bergman said.;    A third person, alsounidentified, was slightly injured, apparently while trying to get away fromthe shooting, said Detective Don Blocker of the Metro-Dade County PoliceDepartment.;    Yellow Cab dispatcher Tommy Duenas said he took a call andsent a cab to a Hialeah, Fla., address. A man in his early 20s wearing a whiteT-shirt and jeans got in and asked to be taken to Alamo, the driver toldDuenas.;    As he was getting out of the cab, Duenas said, the passenger toldthe driver, &quot;I'm going to get these people for firing me.&quot;;    Duenas said hisdriver called in to report the incident.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Knight Ridder News Service  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  Miami  </CITY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  SAN JOSE MERCURY NEWS  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910302  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Saturday  </DAY><MONTH>  March  </MONTH><PG.COL>  8E  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  383  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Saturday March 2, 199100062017,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>